                                a(href="https://github.com/letatanu/DeepHomography") Deep Image Homography Estimation
                            .subheading.mb-3 Python/Pytorch/OpenCV/Numpy/Matplotlib/Jupyter Notebook
                            ul.lead
                                li This project is the unofficial implementation of the paper 
                                    a(href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/1606.03798.pdf") Deep Image Homography Estimation. 
                                li A homography is a mapping from a projective space (image) P to Q. 
                                li From this network, it will estimate a 4-point homography parameterization which maps the four corners from one image into the second image.
                                li As a result, the average corner error is 
                                ul
                                    li 6.003 for the train set.
                                    li 6.034 for the validation set.
