                            h3.mb-0 
                                a(href="https://github.com/letatanu/DeepE_noCor_Pytorch") Deep Essential Matrix Estimation without Correspondences
                            .subheading.mb-3 Python/Pytorch/OpenCV/Numpy/Matplotlib
                            ul.lead
                                li Estimating the essential matrix between two frames obtained by a monocular camera in the epipolar geometry.
                                li The designed ConvNet can directly estimate the essential matrix without detecting feature points (correlations) between the two input images. 
                                li In the test set, the visualizing results looked incredible.
                            img.center.img-fluid.img-thumbnail.img-responsive.rounded.mb-2(src='assets/img/DeepF.gif', alt='demo')
                    
                    .d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
                        .flex-grow-1
                            h3.mb-0 
                                a(href="https://github.com/letatanu/AI_Chess") AI Chess
                            .subheading.mb-3 Python/Numpy/Reinforcement Learning
                            ul.lead
                                li Training an agent that can play chess v.s human players by using reinforcement learning. 
                                li The agent was trained on both sides of the player, which reduces the training time by half. 
                                li As a result, the agent wins 100/100 games v.s the Random agent. 
                            img.center.img-fluid.img-thumbnail.img-responsive.rounded.mb-2(src='assets/img/chess.gif', alt='demo')

                    .d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
                        .flex-grow-1
                            h3.mb-0
                                a(href="https://github.com/letatanu/AI_MineSweeper") AI MineSweeper
                            .subheading.mb-3 Python/Numpy/Reinforcement Learning
                            ul.lead
                                li Training an agent that can play minesweeper itself by using reinforcement learning.
                                li The state in the Q-matrix is re-defined so that the agent trained in small sizes of the grid can play on grids with larger sizes. 
                                li As a result, the agent trained in random 5x5 grids with three mines can win 16/1000 random games of 9x9 grids with ten mines. 
                            img.center.img-fluid.img-thumbnail.img-responsive.rounded.mb-2(src='assets/img/minesweeper.gif', alt='demo')
                    .d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
                        .flex-grow-1
                            h3.mb-0 
                                a(href="https://github.com/letatanu/ColorID") Color ID 
                            .subheading.mb-3 Swift/K-mean
                            ul.lead
                                li An iOS application gives the name of the most dominant color in the given image, which is obtained from the photo gallery or camera on the iOS devices. 
                                li It utilizes a machine learning algorithm called k-mean to cluster colors into groups, then takes the average of color values in the most popular group to give the color result. 
                                li Its extension being developed is to provide the palette of the n-dominant colors from the given image.


                    .d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
                        .flex-grow-1
                            h3.mb-0 
                                a(href="https://github.com/letatanu/FlappyBird-AI") Flappy Bird AI
                            .subheading.mb-3 Python/NEAT
                            ul.lead
                                li Using Neuroevolution of augmenting topologies - NEAT to train the agent that can play Flappy Bird itself. 
                                li After four generations, the agent can play the Flappy Bird game well without losing.
                            
                            img.h-75.img-fluid.img-thumbnail.img-responsive.rounded(src='assets/img/flappyBird.gif', alt='demo')

                    .d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
                        .flex-grow-1
                            h3.mb-0 
                                a(href="https://github.com/letatanu/Imager") Imager
                            .subheading.mb-3 ReactJS/Django/OpenCV/Heroku/Computer Vision
                            ul.lead
                                li The full-stack web application for image processing. 
                                li It has two main functions: generate a palette for and apply filters to the given images. 
                                ul 
                                    li Palette generation detects n-most dominant colors. 
                                    li The applying filters are Gaussian, detail enhances, and grayscale. 

                            ul.list-group.list-group-horizontal-sm
